[thinking] **Considering dynamic access issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm noticing that the generated index resources in the test jar are included, which could lead to dynamic access calls on our public default constructor class. It seems I need to compile for Native Image, especially with tests involving nested public static classes reflective instantiation by ClassIndex from the generated index. I also need to check if reachability metadata can be generated externally by an agent. But, hmm, is it okay for a library to dynamically access user code?
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Exploring ClassIndex and nested classes**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering if ClassIndex might index the interface itself even without any classes. It might include a nested indexed factory class, which raises a question about whether ClassIndex supports nested classes. I think it likely does, but I need to compile a source test that includes these nested classes with a class index processor. Also, I should check if the annotation @IndexSubclasses on a nested interface has source retention.
