",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic access issues**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the generated index resources in the test jar are included, which could lead to dynamic access calls on our public default constructor class. It seems I need to compile for Native Image, especially with tests involving nested public static classes reflective instantiation by ClassIndex from the generated index. I also need to check if reachability metadata can be generated externally by an agent. But, hmm, is it okay for a library to dynamically access user code?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ClassIndex and nested classes**\\n\\nI'm wondering if ClassIndex might index the interface itself even without any classes. It might include a nested indexed factory class, which raises a question about whether ClassIndex supports nested classes. I think it likely does, but I need to compile a source test that includes these nested classes with a class index processor. Also, I should check if the annotation @IndexSubclasses on a nested interface has source retention.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IUYS3nLqb6cgIfvNloa8nFg3|fc_061e314e9a42b0e90169fd560e758c8191a09888c8fde38e24", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"class-index|classindex|annotationProcessor\" -n tests/src/io.fluentlenium/fluentlenium-core/6.0.0/build.gradle build.gradle settings.gradle gradle.properties"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 629, "output": 1087, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23732, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778210300654, "responseId": "resp_061e314e9a42b0e90169fd55fd207481918cc8862424979cbf"}}
